title: Abdominal Hysterectomy ICD9CM
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have a procedure of an abdominal hysterectomy.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have an abdominal hysterectomy procedure.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent abdominal hysterectomy procedures.  Codes used are to be ICD9CM codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.   Exclude codes that represent an abdominal hysterectomy performed using a scope.)
